quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  55,17,"[He is] Lord of the two sunrises and Lord of the two sunsets"
  55,18,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,19,"He merges the two seas [of fresh and salty water] meeting together"
  55,20,yet between them is a barrier so that they do not cross
  55,21,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,22,Out of both of them emerge pearls and coral
  55,23,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,24,To Him belong the sailing ships raised up in the sea like mountains
  55,25,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,26,Everyone on earth will perish
  55,27,"but there will remain the Face of your Lord, full of Majesty and Honor"
  55,28,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,29,All those in the heavens and earth ask of Him; every day He is engaged in some matters
  55,30,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,31,"We will attend to you, O two multitudes [men and jinn]"
  55,32,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,33,"O assembly of jinn and mankind, if you are able to pass beyond the realms of the heavens and earth, then pass; you cannot pass without [Our] authority"
  55,34,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,35,"There will be sent against you flames of fire and smoke, and you will not be able to defend yourselves"
  55,36,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,37,"When the heaven is split asunder and becomes crimson, like red hide"
  55,38,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,39,On that Day no human or jinn will be asked about his sin
  55,40,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"